name: Paleo Biscuits
author: Cindy Anschutz Barbieri
summary: Here is the recipe and they are super yummy. I even cut them open and grilled while I was preparing my zucchini scrambled eggs! I made a yummy blueberry jam and decided to serve with paleo biscuits.
ingredients: ¼ cup coconut oil, melted and cooled
2  large eggs at room temperature, beaten
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C)
Line a baking sheet with parchment paper
Mix almond flour, baking soda, and sea salt together in a bowl; stir in coconut oil until fully incorporated
Stir eggs and honey into almond flour mixture until a dough ball forms
Scoop dough using an ice cream scoop and arrange dough scoops in the parchment paper
Lightly press each piece of dough to create a biscuit shape
Bake in the preheated oven until biscuits are lightly browned, about 15 minutes
